Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 2: And then when I return it, I'll get that $63.95 back?

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, and very soon, like in the next few days, well, depending on how fast your bank moves,

Speaker 2: maybe even right now, I'm refunding you $110.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 1: It was already shipped, like I mentioned.

Speaker 2: I am sorry about that.

Speaker 1: So unfortunately, that part I cannot do.

Speaker 2: But, yeah, I can, okay, so let me refresh your page to make sure that refund went through.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I'm going to email you.

Speaker 1: So the email we have on file, it's T as in Tom, 55708020 at gmail.com,

Speaker 2: and I'm going to send right now the return and refund instructions.

Speaker 1: Now, what I'm going to send is the more extensive option,

Speaker 2: but you're actually in a really good position because you haven't received the product yet,

Speaker 1: and you will in like three or four days, because that means you haven't opened it at all.

Speaker 2: And as long as you do not open the package at all, if you don't want to go to the post office,

Speaker 1: you can just write return to sender on the package and leave it in your post box,

Speaker 2: and your post person will bring it directly back to us,

Speaker 1: and we can use the same tracking number to confirm it's on the way back to us

Speaker 2: and to receive it returned, and then we can process your refund.

Speaker 1: Or if you want to follow the more thorough instructions and you want to go certified mail,

Speaker 2: you do have that option as well.

Speaker 1: And the email I'm sending you right now will have all of that information in there.

Speaker 2: Okay, and I would have to pay for that, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So, yeah, it's up to you.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I just sent that email.

Speaker 2: You will see that refund for 110 pretty soon.

Speaker 1: And, yeah, just once you receive it, you can either write return to sender on the unopened package

Speaker 2: and have a post person bring it back to us, or you can go to the post office if you want a quicker route,

Speaker 1: just because with that more extensive – with those more extensive directions I emailed you,

Speaker 2: if you want to more quickly send them the tracking number

Speaker 1: and get the email team response fairly quickly and mindfully,

Speaker 2: they will be able to get your refund to you a little bit quicker than if you did return to sender.

Speaker 1: Using the tracking number, you offer them via email.

Speaker 2: Gotcha, okay.

Speaker 1: Can you just cancel this account so we don't have to go through this anymore?

Speaker 2: Yes, I did that.

Speaker 2: That's a shame, but, yeah.

Speaker 1: All right, I'll wait to get it and check the refund.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Thomas.

Speaker 1: Bye.
